        <p>He is a <a href="https://www.pluralsight.com/authors/gianni-rosagallina" target="_blank"><strong>Pluralsight Author</strong></a> since 2013 and graduated <em>MSc Information Technology Engineer</em> at the <strong>Polytechnic of Turin</strong> in 2009.</p>
        <p>He has more than 10 years of experience in <strong>Microsoft technologies</strong>. He worked as <em>Software Architect and Consultant</em> for <strong><a href="http://www.bepseng.it" target="_blank">BEPS Engineering</a></strong> from 2007 to 2017, and since 2014 tried to change the Virtual Reality world with his startup <a href="http://www.immotionar.com" target="_blank"><strong>Immotionar</strong></a>, building an amazing cross-platform, easy to use solution (<em>ImmotionRoom</em>) to move naturally inside virtual worlds, with full-body interactions. The dreams ended in early 2017, but his innovative visions are more alive than ever.</p>
